A police station in Urumqi, capital of Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, has offered a reward for anyone who provides information on the terrorist attack at Urumqi South railway station on Wednesday. 
After the attack, local police released photographs of the two dead suspects on Weibo, and called on citizens to provide information, including how they arrived at the site, and where lived before the attack. The police are offering 100,000 yuan to anyone who provides important information or clues related to the attack. 



